Describe an item on which you spent more than expected.
- what it is
- how much you spent on it
- why you bought it
- explain why you think you spent more than expected

I’d like to talk about a laptop that I bought two years ago, which ended up costing me much more than I had originally planned.

At first, I intended to spend around 20 million Vietnamese dong on a basic laptop for my work and studies. However, after doing some research online and visiting a few electronics stores, I eventually paid nearly 30 million, which was quite a large amount of money for me at the time—almost equal to a month’s salary. I remember hesitating a lot before making the final decision.

I decided to buy this laptop because I needed a more powerful device for software development. My old laptop was outdated, overheated easily, and often had compatibility issues with newer software, which was really frustrating.

When comparing different models, I realized that spending more would give me a faster processor, better battery life, and a higher-quality display, all of which significantly improved my productivity.

I think I spent more than expected for two main reasons. Firstly, I was influenced by positive reviews and persuasive advice from sales staff, who emphasized the long-term benefits. Secondly, I convinced myself that it was a worthwhile investment for my work.

Looking back, although it was a big financial decision, it actually saved me a lot of time and stress, so I don’t regret it at all.
